name: Confused sufferer
description:
M.M.I, pt 5: Depression

Void and emptiness is not really the same thing, and it is really confusing. Void often feels like you do not have anything and anyone around you, it feels unsafe and threatening. While emptiness feels like an open infinite plane full of potential and creativity, devoid from harm and risks.

Museum of Mental Incapabilities is a collection of artworks depicting mental health problems and disorders. Explore and understand what it feels like to live with various mental incapacities.
